column1: NOTE 1:  Under the Inflation Reduction Act of 2023, beneficiary coinsurance will be based on 20% of the lower inflation-adjusted payment amount for the quarter and will be reflected as a percentage (that is less than 20%) of the Medicare Part B payment amount. This column reflects the drug copayment amounts which have a coinsurance percentage less than 20%. The Medicare portion of the payment will be increased to the difference between the Medicare Part B payment amount and beneficiary coinsurance, minus any Part B deductible and sequestration.

NOTE 2: In general, the Medicare program payment is 80 percent of the total payment amount and beneficiary coinsurance is 20 percent of the total payment amount. There is no beneficiary coinsurance for most preventive services.  Sections 4104 and 10406 of the Affordable Care Act (ACA) waive coinsurance and the Part B deductible for most preventive services.  These preventive services are identified with a double asterisk (**).

NOTE 3:  In general, payment indicators Z2 and Z3 (certain radiology or diagnostic services) are based on a comparison of the final rates according to the ASC standard ratesetting methodology and the MPFS final rates effective January 1, 2025. For a discussion of the MPFS rates, we refer readers to the CY 2025 MPFS final rule.

NOTE 4:  Triple asterisked codes(***) indicate that the item is a non-opioid alternative covered under Section 4135 of the Consolidated Appropriations Act of 2023 (P.L. 117-328). Separate payments for such covered non-opioid alternatives are subject to a payment limitation of 18 percent of the OPD fee schedule amount for the OPD service (or group of services) with which the non-opioid treatment is furnished.
